<PLACE><ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Cattaraugus</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">New York</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">United States</ENAMEX></PLACE>
<SBODY>4 3
QUIT-CLAIM <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">DEED</ENAMEX>.
This <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">Indenture</ENAMEX>, Made this <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Fifth
of our Lord one thousand eight hundred and eighty two</TIMEX> Between <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Gideon Olean</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Cattaraugus</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX>
of the first part, and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Anna J. Haman</ENAMEX> of the same place.
of the second part,
Witnesseth, That the said party of the first part, in consideration of the sum of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">One Dollar</NUMEX> ( <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">$1/6/10</NUMEX>)
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">him</ENAMEX> in hand paid by the said party of the second part, the receipt whereof is
hereby confessed and acknowledged, hath bargained, sold, remised and <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">QUTT-CLAIMED</ENAMEX>, and by these Presents do th bargain, sell, remise <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">and Quit-Claim</ENAMEX>
unto the said party of the second part,
and to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX> forever, ALL that tract or parcel of land situate in
the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Village of Olean</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Cattaraugus</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX>. Known and distinguished on a
map of <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF.loc">said Village</ENAMEX> made by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">F.J. Gosseline</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="TITLE">Esq.</ENAMEX> bounded and described as follows: Commenc-
ing at the Northwest corner of lot number thirty five ( 35) in Block number one <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">hundred and
four ( 104)</NUMEX> running thence Southerly <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">forty</NUMEX> feet ( <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">40</NUMEX>) thence easterly to first street <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">one hundred</NUMEX> 
feet ( <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">100</NUMEX>) thence northerly along <ENAMEX TYPE="STRUCTURE">First street</ENAMEX> <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">forty</NUMEX> feet ( <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">40</NUMEX>), thence westerly <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">one hundred</NUMEX> feet
( <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">100</NUMEX>) to the place of beginning. 
This deed is given and executed subject to a certain <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">Indenture</ENAMEX> of Mortgage given to secure. 
the payment of the sum of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">Seven hundred twenty six dollars and thirty seven cents</NUMEX> and the in- 
terest thereon and to become due thereon, made by the said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Charles L. Hamar</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">wife</ENAMEX> and running to <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Helen G. Strong</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">Administratrix</ENAMEX>, said mortgage bearing date about the
<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">15th day of December 1881</TIMEX>, and also subject to the payment of a certain Mortgage with 
interest thereon and to become due thereon made by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Eliza Hamar</ENAMEX> to <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Charles Gillingham</ENAMEX> 
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">William D. Moore</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Albert Judge</ENAMEX>, and assigned by <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">them</ENAMEX> to <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Weston Brothers</ENAMEX> and by <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">them-
to</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Helen G. Strong</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">administratrix</ENAMEX> on or about the <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">15th day of December 1881</TIMEX>, said mort- gage was given for the security of the payment of the sum of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">six hundred seventy three dollars and sixty three cents</NUMEX>.
Together with all and singular the hereditaments and appurtenances thereto belonging or in any wise appertaining, and the reversion and reversions,
remainder and remainders, rents, issues and profits thereof, and all the estate, right, title, interest, claim and demand whatsoever of the said part if of the
first part, either in law or equity, of, in and to the above bargained premises, with the said hereditaments and appurtenances, to Have and to Hold the said
to the said party of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>, to the sole and only proper benefit and behoof of the said party of the second
part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX> forever.
In <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">Witness</ENAMEX> Whereoff, The party of the first part hath hereunto set <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> hand and seal the <TIMEX TYPE="COREF.dat">day and year first above written</TIMEX>.
Sealed and Delivered in Presence of --
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">G. H. Strong</ENAMEX>
[ L. S.]
[ L. S.]
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">STATE OF NEW YORK</ENAMEX>.
County of ⌨⌨⌨ U <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Dillage</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Olean</ENAMEX> ⎬ s on the <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Fifth
day of May
in the year one thousand eight hundred and
eighty two</TIMEX> before <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX>, the subscriber, personally appeared <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Gideon H. Strong</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Olean</ENAMEX>
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX> personally known to be the same person described in and <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">who</ENAMEX> executed the within
instrument, and eey acknowledged that the executed the same; the
ed apeirateeneminationby meapart from hersaidusbondeinewledged that sheexecuted the same freely and withestany fee or compulsion of <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> saidhusband
All erasures and interlineations in this deed were made before the execution and delivery
of this instrument.
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">C. P. Moulton</ENAMEX>,
<ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Notary Public</ENAMEX>.
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Sedom th</ENAMEX>
<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">___ day of May 1882</TIMEX>
at__<TIMEX TYPE="TIME">o'clock P. M.</TIMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">M. J. Rich</ENAMEX> =====
⌨ ⌨ &
</SBODY>

QUIT-CLAIM <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">DEED</ENAMEX>.
This <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">Indenture</ENAMEX>, Made this <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Fifth
of our Lord one thousand eight hundred and eighty two</TIMEX> Between <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Gideon Olean</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Cattaraugus</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX>
of the first part, and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Anna J. Haman</ENAMEX> of the same place.
of the second part,
Witnesseth, That the said party of the first part, in consideration of the sum of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">One Dollar</NUMEX> ( <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">$1/6/10</NUMEX>)
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">him</ENAMEX> in hand paid by the said party of the second part, the receipt whereof is
hereby confessed and acknowledged, hath bargained, sold, remised and <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">QUTT-CLAIMED</ENAMEX>, and by these Presents do th bargain, sell, remise <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">and Quit-Claim</ENAMEX>
unto the said party of the second part,
and to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX> forever, ALL that tract or parcel of land situate in
the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Village of Olean</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Cattaraugus</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX>. Known and distinguished on a
map of <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF.loc">said Village</ENAMEX> made by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">F.J. Gosseline</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="TITLE">Esq.</ENAMEX> bounded and described as follows: Commenc-
ing at the Northwest corner of lot number thirty five ( 35) in Block number one <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">hundred and
four ( 104)</NUMEX> running thence Southerly <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">forty</NUMEX> feet ( <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">40</NUMEX>) thence easterly to first street <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">one hundred</NUMEX> 
feet ( <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">100</NUMEX>) thence northerly along <ENAMEX TYPE="STRUCTURE">First street</ENAMEX> <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">forty</NUMEX> feet ( <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">40</NUMEX>), thence westerly <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">one hundred</NUMEX> feet
( <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">100</NUMEX>) to the place of beginning. 
This deed is given and executed subject to a certain <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">Indenture</ENAMEX> of Mortgage given to secure. 
the payment of the sum of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">Seven hundred twenty six dollars and thirty seven cents</NUMEX> and the in- 
terest thereon and to become due thereon, made by the said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Charles L. Hamar</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">wife</ENAMEX> and running to <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Helen G. Strong</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">Administratrix</ENAMEX>, said mortgage bearing date about the
<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">15th day of December 1881</TIMEX>, and also subject to the payment of a certain Mortgage with 
interest thereon and to become due thereon made by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Eliza Hamar</ENAMEX> to <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Charles Gillingham</ENAMEX> 
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">William D. Moore</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Albert Judge</ENAMEX>, and assigned by <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">them</ENAMEX> to <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Weston Brothers</ENAMEX> and by <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">them-
to</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Helen G. Strong</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">administratrix</ENAMEX> on or about the <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">15th day of December 1881</TIMEX>, said mort- gage was given for the security of the payment of the sum of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">six hundred seventy three dollars and sixty three cents</NUMEX>.
Together with all and singular the hereditaments and appurtenances thereto belonging or in any wise appertaining, and the reversion and reversions,
remainder and remainders, rents, issues and profits thereof, and all the estate, right, title, interest, claim and demand whatsoever of the said part if of the
first part, either in law or equity, of, in and to the above bargained premises, with the said hereditaments and appurtenances, to Have and to Hold the said
to the said party of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>, to the sole and only proper benefit and behoof of the said party of the second
part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX> forever.
In <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">Witness</ENAMEX> Whereoff, The party of the first part hath hereunto set <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> hand and seal the <TIMEX TYPE="COREF.dat">day and year first above written</TIMEX>.
Sealed and Delivered in Presence of --
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">G. H. Strong</ENAMEX>
[ L. S.]
